The BA in Kinesiology - Movement Studies Option is an approved match to the AA-T in Kinesiology.
Lower Division Activity Breadth Course Requirement

﻿In sections below where the student is directed to select courses and there is a note "Only lower division courses listed," upper division courses are also available. See the University Catalog for the full listing of degree requirements.

Students must complete 5 courses from at least 5 of the 7 groups listed below (5-10 units):

  • Aquatics
  • Dance, Tumbling, or Gymnastics
  • Individual or Dual
  • Outdoor Education/Recreation
  • Personal Defense or Combatives
  • Team Sports
  • Weight Training or Fitness

Students must select 1 of 2 advising patterns for completion of the major course requirements.

  • The 2 advising patterns are: Coaching and Administration Pattern, and Fitness and Wellness Pattern.
  • Both patterns list KINE 247 (see below) as an elective course students may choose.
  • The required courses and remaining elective courses for both patterns are at the upper division level.
  • See the University Catalog for a full listing of the degree requirements.
